<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Without playing a single game, Baltimore Orioles slugger Trey Mancini delivered one of the highlights of the 2020 MLB season on Monday by completing his six-month chemotherapy treatment.</p>

<p>Mancini, who was diagnosed with colon cancer during spring training, sat out the season following his March 12 surgery.</p>

<p>'What a six months it has been,' Mancini's girlfriend, Sara Perlman, wrote on social media. 'I've never been more proud.'</p>

